text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia spinosissima is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt region of Western Australia.The shrub typically grows to a height of 0.2 to 1.5 metres (0.7 to 4.9 ft). It blooms from August to September and produces yellow flowers.
